<Base title="About · Pangaea">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    Pangaea is a hub for the spoken and the written word, by{' '}
    <a href="https://adampang.com">Adam Pang</a>. The plan is simple: write daily, ship daily,
    world-build relentlessly.
  </p>

  <p>
    My three loves are music, philosophy, and business. Pangaea is the place where they share a
    map. Each post might be a song that's been on repeat, a paragraph that wouldn't leave my head,
    a tool I'm using, a quote I keep coming back to. Sometimes a longer essay, sometimes just a
    photo. The format is loose; the cadence is not.
  </p>

  <h2>Why "Pangaea"</h2>
  <p>
    Pangaea was the supercontinent. Everything together, before the world broke apart into
    separate places. That's the metaphor. Music, philosophy, business: they're not separate to
    me, and this is the place I keep them on the same map.
  </p>

  <h2>Lineage</h2>
  <p>
    With debts to the <em>Whole Earth Catalog</em>, <a href="https://sive.rs">Derek Sivers</a>,{' '}
    <a href="https://paulgraham.com">Paul Graham</a>, <a href="https://waitbutwhy.com">Tim Urban</a>,
    and <a href="https://tim.blog">Tim Ferriss</a>'s 5 Bullet Friday. The long tradition of
    writers who own their words at their own URLs.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <p class="meta">
    Tell me what you think: <a href="https://adampang.com/hi">adampang.com/hi</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
